name: Carla the Poet - Imposter Syndrome feat. Rey Morado

metadata.description:
Have you ever gotten to the next level and wondered if you belonged there? Life lately has been what I always imagined it was supposed to be, and yet I still have this lingering unease as I step into the success I’ve created for myself.

  Coming from a single-parent home and contending with the struggles that entailed, I made the commitment to myself that I would transcend my circumstances through my own effort and creativity. I’ve prepared myself to work harder, to do better, to become greater… but one thing I wasn’t prepared for was the feeling of not belonging in the life I had dreamed of.

  Imposter Syndrome speaks to the phenomenon of “arrival fallacy,” in which you’ve achieved what you set out to do… but things but still feel uneasy in the place that your success has brought you to.
Accompanied by fellow artist Rey Morado of ReignCloud Music Group, with production by Dav, Imposter Syndrome is the pure expression of the fear, doubt, and anxiety that comes from leaving behind the patterns of your old life and carving out something new for yourself.
